text: Teranga is a genus of southeastern Asian cellar spiders first described by B. A. Huber, J. Eberle & D. Dimitrov in 2018. ==Species== it contains four species: *Teranga cibodas (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Java) *Teranga domingo (Huber, 2016) — Philippines *Teranga kerinci (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Sumatra) *Teranga matutum (Huber, 2016) — Philippines ==References== ==External links== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Pholcidae
title: Teranga
